  <primary_outcome>
    <measure>The primary efficacy variable is the number of responders with a very good asthma symptom control defined as requiring no rapid acting beta agonist (RABA) between the 2. and 6th week of intervention (end of trial)</measure>
  </primary_outcome>
  <secondary_outcome>
    <measure>the number of patients requiring at least five times RABA between the 2. and 6th week, the number of patients with an increase of FEV1 7.5%, the symptom score, symptom free days, rescue medication, presence of allergy RAST &gt; 2, concentration of eNO, PD20</measure>
  </secondary_outcome>
