  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Male or female patients age 4 -6 years

          -  Diagnosis of mild intermittent bronchial asthma (Step I-II) in the past 6 - 12 months
             as stated by the investigator:

          -  Use of inhaled beta-2-agonists &lt; 1/week (max 3 puff /d)

          -  Exacerbation-free interval &gt; 4 weeks prior to visit 1

          -  The written informed consent of parents after received written and oral information
             about the aim, purpose and risks of the study must be present

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Asthma severity ≥ Step 2

          -  Severe concomitant diseases

          -  Suspected non-compliance

          -  age below 4 and age above 7 years

          -  last study participation &lt; 30 days
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
